The statement added: 'The campus administration conducted an investigation and the students involved were disciplined according to the Student Code of Conduct.'

Mr Green however, said: 'It wasn't a fight, it was really an assault.

The father says he now fears for the safety of his daughter and other children at the school.

'My concern is Cy-Ridge have no system in place to protect my child while she’s in school. And it’s not just my child. It could be anybody’s child,' he said.

